<TITLE> Yunus signs Saifur's condolence book </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus signed the condolence book for former finance minister M Saifur Rahman at BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia's political office in Gulshan on Monday. Envoys from Japan and the Vatican City were also among those who signed the book on the day, said Maruf Kamal Khan, the BNP chairperson's press secretary, who added the book would be open to the general public on Tuesday at the chairperson's office. Foreign diplomats, including the US ambassador, also signed the book on Sunday. The condolence book was opened on Sunday, a day after Rahman was killed in a car crash. India's prime minister Manmohan Singh, himself a former finance minister, has also condoled the death of Saifur Rahman, Bangladesh's longest serving finance minister. 
